Adverbs  of comparison

When we want to show a difference between how two things are done, we can use the words much, a little, a bit, a lot, slightly, far, more, less.

If you want to show a big difference:

He plays much better than I do.

She comes to work far earlier than I do.

They took a lot longer to get there.

If you want to show a small difference:

She did slightly less successful in her second exam.

He runs slightly faster than I do.

She drives a bit slower than I do.

It tooks a little longer to get there.

Introducing examples:

When we want to introduce an example in a text, we can use the following:

For example, look at the training of pilots.

Example (of this) include the two pilot training programs.

One example (of this) is the pilot traning program.

